{"heading":"The way of the transgressor is hard—Evil pursues sinners—He who does not discipline his children hates them.","number":13,"verseCount":25,"verses":[[1,["A wise son ",["heareth",["clarity-word"]]," his father’s instruction: but a scorner heareth not rebuke."]],[2,["A man shall eat good by the fruit of ",["his",["clarity-word"]]," mouth: but the soul of the transgressors ",["shall eat",["clarity-word"]]," violence."]],[3,["He that keepeth his ",["mouth",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Silence","tg/silence"],"."]]]," keepeth his life: ",["but",["clarity-word"]]," he that openeth wide his ",["lips",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Gossip","tg/gossip"],"."]]]," shall have destruction."]],[4,["The soul of the ",["sluggard",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Apathy","tg/apathy"],"; ",["Laziness","tg/laziness"],"."]]]," desireth, and ",["hath",["clarity-word"]]," nothing: but the soul of the diligent shall be made fat."]],[5,["A righteous ",["man",["clarity-word"]]," ",["hateth",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Hate","tg/hate"],"."]]]," lying: but a wicked ",["man",["clarity-word"]]," is loathsome, and cometh to shame."]],[6,[["Righteousness",["study-note-ref","a",[["Prov. 11:5 (3–6)","ot/prov/11.5"],"; ",["D&C 133:44","dc-testament/dc/133.44"],"."]]]," keepeth ",["him that is",["clarity-word"]]," upright in the way: but wickedness overthroweth the sinner."]],[7,["There is that maketh himself ",["rich",["study-note-ref","a",[["Prov. 11:24","ot/prov/11.24"],"; ",["Matt. 16:26","nt/matt/16.26"],"."]]],", yet ",["hath",["clarity-word"]]," nothing: ",["there is",["clarity-word"]]," that maketh himself poor, yet ",["hath",["clarity-word"]]," great ",["riches",["study-note-ref","b",[["D&C 6:7","dc-testament/dc/6.7"],"."]]],"."]],[8,["The ransom of a man’s life ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," his riches: but the poor heareth not rebuke."]],[9,["The light of the righteous rejoiceth: but the ",["lamp",["study-note-ref","a",[["Job 18:5","ot/job/18.5"],"; ",["Prov. 24:20","ot/prov/24.20"],"."]]],